            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Hd1e108">Rubrica 12</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De facilitate et difficultate</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#P"/>De facilitate / et difficultate
               <lb ed="#P"/>capitulum xii:-:-:-:-:-
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref>Psalmista. psalmus. ci.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e123">Maledictione cuius 
               <lb ed="#P"/>os plenum est / et amaritudine sub
               <lb ed="#P"/>lingua eius labor / et dolor.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e133">
               <lb ed="#P" n="18"/>
               ¶ <ref>Isaias propheta. c. 26</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e137">Semita iusti recta est
        <lb ed="#P" n="19"/>rectus callis iusti ad ambulandum</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e144">
               <lb ed="#P" n="20"/>
               ¶ <ref>Aristoteles ethicorum. li. 2. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e148">Circa diffici
        <lb ed="#P" n="21" break="no"/>lius semper et ars fit et virtus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e154"> /
      <ref>Idem de me
        <lb ed="#P" n="22" break="no"/>moria et reminiscentia:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e156">Sunt magis remini
        <lb ed="#P" n="23" break="no"/>scibiliora quecumque ordinationem habent.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e164"> /
      <ref>Idem
        <lb ed="#P" n="24"/>iconomicorum libro i. in fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e166">Oportet vnumquodque
        <lb ed="#P" n="25"/>in loco suo poni. Sic enim paratum existens
        <lb ed="#P" n="26"/>non queretur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e176"> /
      <ref>Idem rethoricorum libro i. c. 10.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e178">Faci
        <lb ed="#P" n="27" break="no"/>lia sunt quecumque fiunt sine tristitia: vel in mo
        <lb ed="#P" n="28" break="no"/>dico tempore. Difficile enim determinantur aut
        <lb ed="#P" n="29"/>tristitia aut multitudine temporis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e188"> /
      <ref>Idem elemen
        <lb ed="#P" n="30" break="no"/>torum libro i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e190">Difficile est simul multa conspicere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e196">
               <lb ed="#P" n="31"/>
               / <ref>Li. 2. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e200">Prouidere quidem difficile est: per
        <lb ed="#P" n="32"/>vacationem autem videre facile. Inuento faci
        <lb ed="#P" n="33" break="no"/>le est addere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e209">
               <lb ed="#P" n="34"/>
               ¶ <ref>Terentius in heautontumerumenos. c. 17</ref>
        <lb ed="#P" n="35"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e213">Nulla res est tanta facilis: quin difficilis fiet
        <lb ed="#P" n="36"/>quam inuitus facias.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e221">
               <lb ed="#P" n="37"/>
               ¶ <ref>Salustius in catalinario:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e225">Que quisque fa
        <lb ed="#P" n="38" break="no"/>cilia factu putat equo animo accipit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e231">
               <lb ed="#P" n="39"/>
               ¶ <ref>Tullius retho. artis vereris li. 2. c. 12.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e235">Fa
        <lb ed="#P" n="40" break="no"/>cile fieri id dicimus quod sine magno aut
        <lb ed="#P" n="41"/>sine vllo labore sumptu molestia quam breuis
        <lb ed="#P" n="42"/>simo tempore confici potest: difficile autem
        <lb ed="#P" n="43"/>fieri quod quamquam laboris sumptus molestie lon
        <lb ed="#P" n="44" break="no"/>gitudinis indiget: atque omnes: aut plurimas
        <lb ed="#P" n="45"/>aut maximas causas habet difficultatis: tantum <!--70.xml-->
        <cb ed="#P" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#P" n="46"/>his susceptis difficultatibus compleri atque
        <lb ed="#P" n="47"/>ad exitum perduci potest.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e260"> /
      <ref>Idem de orato
        <lb ed="#P" n="48"/>re li. 3. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e262">Facilius est apta dissoluere quam
        <lb ed="#P" n="49"/>dissipata connectere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e270"> /
      <ref>Idem super timeum pla
        <lb ed="#P" n="50" break="no"/>tonis de essentina mundi:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e272">Difficillimum est in
        <lb ed="#P" n="51"/>omni conquisitione rationis exordium.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e280">
               <lb ed="#P" n="52"/>
               ¶ <ref>Ouidius epistolarum. 12. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e284">Ultimus est
        <lb ed="#P" n="53"/>aliqua decipere arte labor.<ref>Epistola. 16.</ref>
        <lb ed="#P" n="54"/>Difficilem culpe suspicor esse viam.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e293"> /
      <ref>De tri
        <lb ed="#P" n="55" break="no"/>stibus libro. 3. c. 11.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e295">In causa facili cui ius
        <lb ed="#P" n="56"/>licet esse dissertur. Et minime vires frange
        <lb ed="#P" n="57" break="no"/>re quassa valent.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e305">
               <lb ed="#P" n="58"/>
               ¶ <ref>Seneca de ira libro. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e309">Nihil est difficile
        <lb ed="#P" n="59"/>et arduum quod non humana mens vincat: et
        <lb ed="#P" n="60"/>in familiaritatem perducat assidua medita
        <lb ed="#P" n="61" break="no"/>tio.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e319"> /
      <ref>Idem de consolatione ad helbiam:</ref>
        <lb ed="#P" n="62"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e321">Nihil homini natura quod necessarium facie
        <lb ed="#P" n="63" break="no"/>bat fecit operosum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e329">
               <lb ed="#P" n="64"/>
               ¶ <ref>Lex aucten. ti. de monachis.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e333">§. scimus. Non <!--add '§' to ref tag?-->
        <lb ed="#P" n="65"/>facilis est vite mutatio sed cum magno ani
        <lb ed="#P" n="66" break="no"/>mi fit labore.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e341">
               <lb ed="#P" n="67"/>
               ¶ <ref>Uegecius de re militari li. i. c. 20.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e345">Quotti
        <lb ed="#P" n="68" break="no"/>dianus vsus non laborat: etsi onerosa gesta
        <lb ed="#P" n="69" break="no"/>uerit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e353"> /
      <ref>Libro. 3 ti. 17.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e355">Omne opus diffi
        <lb ed="#P" n="70" break="no"/>cile videtur antequam tentes.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e362">
               <lb ed="#P" n="71"/>
               ¶ <ref>Augustinus in epigrama. prosperi. 65.
        <lb ed="#P" n="72"/>emp.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e366">Difficilia et laboriosa sunt figmenta
        <lb ed="#P" n="73"/>mendacii: qui autem vult verum dicere: non
        <lb ed="#P" n="74"/>laborat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e376">
               <lb ed="#P" n="75"/>
               ¶ <ref>Gualterius de castellione alexandreidos
        <lb ed="#P" n="76"/>8. libro.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e380">O quam difficile visu sors prouehit
        <lb ed="#P" n="77"/>actus Lubrica mortales: et quos ascende
        <lb ed="#P" n="78" break="no"/>re fecit: Quam facile euereit: magno fortuna
        <lb ed="#P" n="79"/>labore.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e392">
               <lb ed="#P" n="80"/>
               ¶ <ref>Mattheus vindocinensis in poetria: par.
        <lb ed="#P" n="81"/>2. et fi. cap. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e396">Leuius est inferre vulnera quam
        <lb ed="#P" n="82"/>sanare.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e404">
               <lb ed="#P" n="83"/>
               ¶ <ref>Ganfred. in poetria. c. 30.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e408">Facti grauitas
        <lb ed="#P" n="84"/>cuicumque volenti. Est leuis et leuitas animo
        <lb ed="#P" n="85"/>cuicumque rebelli Est grauis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e416">
               <lb ed="#P" n="86"/>
               ¶ <ref>Ricardus iudex venusinus:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e420">Est labor in la
        <lb ed="#P" n="87" break="no"/>biis mendacia composituris. Uera locutu
        <lb ed="#P" n="88" break="no"/>ris non labor vllus inest.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e428">
               <lb ed="#P" n="89"/>
               ¶ <ref>Montanarius in luna cleri:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e432">Leuiter fit
        <lb ed="#P" n="90"/>quicquid amatur. <!--71.xml-->
               </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
